headline: Intel CEO Lip-Bu Tan Sells Another $18 Million of This Tech Stock
summary: Intel  CEO Lip-Bu Tan continues to reduce his stake in  Credo Technology Group Holding  a provider of high-speed connectivity solutions.  Tan, a Credo director, sold 225,770 shares over June 16 and 18 for a total of $18 million, an average price of $79.94 each.  Tan sold the shares through an investment vehicle that now owns 559,428 Credo shares, according to forms he filed with the Securities and Exchange Commission.
